'''Sidus''' ([[Hangul]]: 싸이더스 픽쳐스, formerly called '''Uno Film''', '''Sidus''' and '''Sidus FNH''') is a film production and distribution company based in [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]. Established in 1995, the company has distributed and  produced over 70 films since their founding.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/view/stview.php?no=2005051318253731749&type=1&outlink=1|title=싸이더스픽쳐스, 좋은영화와 합병|accessdate=28 April 2014|date=13 May 2005|work=Star News|deadurl=no}} </ref>

==History==
Sidus was founded by Mr. James Hyung Soon Kim after taking over Uno Films, which began in 1995. The company changed its name to Sidus in 2000 and merged with EBM, a talent management firm. EBM would split from Sidus in 2005 and be renamed [[iHQ (company)|iHQ]]. Also in 2005, Sidus was acquired by KT corporation, under which Sidus began investing in, and distributing domestic and foreign films.<ref name="Korean Producer Sidus Distributes">{{cite web|title=Korean Producer Sidus Distributes|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/korean-producer-sidus-distribute-142753|website=Hollywood Reporter|publisher=Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=1 August 2016}}</ref><ref name="Korean Sidus Sets Film Fund">{{cite web|last1=Paquet|first1=Darcy|title=Korean Sidus Sets Film Fund|url=https://variety.com/2006/film/news/korean-sidus-sets-film-fund-1117954060/|website=Variety|publisher=Variety|accessdate=1 August 2016}}</ref> In 2014, Sidus was acquired by Locus Corporation, which is headed by Sidus's original founder Mr. Kim. 

Throughout its history, Sidus has produced over 70 films and continues to work in film production, distribution, and investment on an international scale.<ref>{{cite web|title=Company |work=Sidus Pictures |url=http://www.sidus.com/eng/company.asp |accessdate=2014-09-05}}</ref>

